flowRoot.flowPara: The United Nations' (UN) International Day for the Elimination of Violence against Women, globally observed on 25 November, is aimed at raising public awareness of violence against women and triggering action to end this global scourge. It was started in 1999 to commemorate the Mirabal sisters, the political activists in the Dominican Republic who were assassinated in 1960 for opposing the dictator, Rafael Trujillo.
